grams Graduation Application GPA Calculations Majors, Minors and Certificates Online Academic Resources Pre-Law Transfer FAQs UNT's Academic Standards Office of Student Advising Mission of the Office of Student Advising: The office mission is to advise, teach, assist and empower students to define, clarify and achieve academic and personal goals through professional, caring service. Get Advised Now! Call (940) 565-2051 to set up your academic advising appointment today. REMINDER: All first-time-in-college students as well as students who are on academic alert or probation are required to come in for advising prior to registration. Graduate Student Travel Support Grants Travel Support Grants of up to $500 are available for academically successful graduate students to assist in conducting or presenting research. Student's overall GPA must be 3.5 or above and have completed 18 hours at UNT to apply. Preference will be given to students who have not received a previous award. Only one award per student per academic year (September 1 - August 31). The deadline for Summer 2017 applications has past, check back in August/September for Fall 2017 applications. Thinking about UNT? It's easy to apply online. Join us and discover why we're the choice of over 37,000 students. Apply now Contact Us (940) 565-2492 class@unt.edu Visit Us General Academic Building 210 Send Us Mail 1155 Union Circle #305189 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 University of North Texas Explore our degrees Take a tour Get financial aid Apply online Find a person Register for classes Follow UNT on social media Disclaimer AA/EOE/ADA Privacy Statement Electronic Accessibility State of Texas Online Emergency Preparedness THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information UNT Compliance Hotline Governors Committee on People with Disabilities Texas Veterans Portal UNT Home 